    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - COMPONENTS - BLOWER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BLOWER</title>
        <para>The blower fan (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601406">Figure 6</hotlnk>) provides air circulation through the heater and evaporator
            cores and delivers the treated air to the cab interior. Vehicles with air conditioning have a powerful
            permanent magnet type blower motor which utilizes a vent for efficient motor cooling. Vehicles with the
            heater only system have a smaller permanent magnet type blower motor.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1601406" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601406" filename="../figg16/g1601406.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
